{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"0b120fcc-92b4-4ff1-9bab-8e1a5f8220b9","content":"Here's what I found:\n\n**`my_app/views.py:3`** — `datetime.now()`\n```python\nnow = datetime.now()\n```\n\nThis is the only untestable static call in the project. It's hard to mock because it's called directly as a bare static method.\n\n**Recommended fix:** Use Django's `django.utils.timezone.now` instead, which is easier to mock, or inject a clock dependency:\n\n```python\nfrom django.utils import timezone\n\ndef index(request):\n    now = timezone.now()\n    return render(request, 'index.html', {'time': now})\n```\n\nThen in tests you can simply patch it:\n```python\nfrom unittest.mock import patch\nwith patch('django.utils.timezone.now', return_value=...):\n    ...\n```\n\nWant me to apply the fix?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"9330abcd-3b75-454b-ab45-258e02616b7d","outputTokens":199,"requestId":"7C28:1136F1:178DF1F:1AD736E:69F95C83"},"id":"3b46f7a1-6d69-41f6-a363-f86689aa6fcf","timestamp":"2026-05-05T02:57:11.584Z","parentId":"2b1c86b8-445a-4697-a307-aa695823ab04"}
